Column.Name: Validation
Parent Structure

Label.Text:
There are 3 kinds of criteria: Gateway, Mandatory and Discretionary. Below is an explanation of how each behaves in the system.
Gateway - Criteria is assessed as 'Pass or Fail', there isn't a scoring component. For example: "The respondent has existing OH&S Policies". The user setting up a procurement cannot manually change which gateway criteria is required.
Mandatory - This is scored. The user setting up a procurement cannot manually change which mandatory criteria is required.
Discretionary - This is scored. The user setting up a procurement can manually change which discretionary criteria is required.

Information.Text: Tickbox the checkbox below will set a line as a 'Category' which is a basic grouping mechanism to putting related criteria under a single heading.
